messages.content: Iuvenis’ station of awakening is altered somewhat to have some more futuristic elements, and one of his circles is brighter red. “Wh-Where am I...?”
Iuvenis was sitting at the edge of the station, his legs dangling, he looks over to Wanderer, “Oh, h-h-hey Wander.”
“Hi, Iuvenis...” she sat down next to him, tail swishing back and forth.
“What’s u-up?” He softly spoke, looking into the abyss of...whatever the station was raised from.
“Well...not a whole lot if I’m being honest...just...thinking about things.”
“S-Same.......what s-stuff th-though..”
“...I miss mom and dad...”
“Oh......th-that’s...rough..”
She nodded. “But theyre...Y’know...busy...”
“Y-Yeah.....it m-may not h-h-help but....I’m su-sure you’ll s-see them again-in...”
“I...I hope so...”
“M-Me too....yo-your parents a-are nice pe-people....”
“They are! They’re both great Muns!”
“I w-Wish I could m-m-meet them..”
“M-Maybe, when we get back, you can...”
"I-I'm sure they'd like to meet you."
“Y-You think....?” A twinge of Hope In his eyes as he looks up.
She nodded. "Yeah, I do!"
“Th-that’s...nice...” he mumbled. Playing with his fingers.
“I-Is...something wrong with you? You seem kind of sad too...”
“Hmm..? Oh,...j-just thinking ab-about...h-h-him..”
“... Y-Your brother...?”

“Yeah...I tried to make him here but.....” he points to a blackish goop on the far side of the station “it didn’t go well.” Iuvenis sighs, “the only lead I have to finding him is someone I don’t know the location of anymore.....”
“Ohh...” she looked back at the goo. “...Who is that someone?”

“His best frien.....w-w-well I’m n-not sure if th-they’re still that....a mun n-named....Solum...all I remember is that h-he jo-joined the p-p-plasma side n-not too long a-ago....I do-don’t e-even know if h-he’s still a-alive-I....even if h-he is....wo-would he be w-willing to he-help? W-What if....he kil....”
“H-Hey! Y-You cant think like th-that!” She places a quick hand on his shoulder.
“S-Sorry...I j-just....don’t ev-even know...**w-where this g-g-guy is!**..” he throws his hands up in the air
“Not to m-mention he’s o-o-on the op-opposite side o-of the revolution...”
She shudders, looking nervous. “O-Oh...”
“Y-Yeah...Weird c-considering ho-how the plasma t-t-treated us...Do they ev-even have a-any muns on-n their s-s-side?.”
“I should hope not...or...do you *think* there are plasma who could be nice? I know it sounds crazy, but...”
“I-I don’t k-know... ma-maybe? It’s k-k-kinda hard to b-believe with the t-things they d-d-done if they ha-have a single nice-e bone in t-their body...”
She nodded slowly. “I-I don’t know what to believe...about anything...”

“ B-But I kn-know I gotta f-find him...I g-g-gotta! It’s w-what big br-brother  w-would’ve wa-wanted!” He pumps his fists in the air with determination, “I’ll find y-you Solum! A-A-And then Brother t-too! So W-watch out!”
“A-And I’ll help...any way I can.”
“T-Thank you....I-It means a-a lot to m-m-me....” he gives a big smile,
"That's what friends do, right?" She smiled back.
"They help each other."
“Y-Yeah......I’m gl-glad we’re f-friends...” he said, before laughing, “Nobody c-can stop t-t-the two o-of us!”
"Y-Yeah! Me too! W-We'll be the best team the multiverse's ever seen!" She giggled.
“Y-You hear t-that plasma? Your d-d-days are nu-numbered!” He gleefully shouts into the void of his mindscape, the entire circle glowing, almost proudly.
Wanderer grinned happily, looking down at the glowing station at her feet. "We're coming for you!!" She cheered.
As they cheered, the place rumbled as the pillar holding the station lowered a bit, now...even though it’s hard to see, globs of stars dotted the void surrounding them,
"What the-?!" She gasped, clinging onto him as the station rumbled.
“A-Ah!” He hugged Wanderer tightly, squeezing his eyes shut as the place kept shaking and lowering before an abrupt stop.
“....Wh-What was that...?” She asked, looking a little startled.
“I-I don’t k-know....bu-but it stopped...” he looked equally as startled
"I...I hope it doesn't happen again..." (OH IT WILL i'm sure of it)

((Little did they know-))
“I-I’m sure it w-won’t...be-besides...none of the-e mons-monsters showed u-up so....it m-must be a g-g-good thing.”
"Y-You have monsters...?" She shuddered.
“Y-Yeah? Do-doesn’t e-everyone?”
"M-Maybe...? I've only been in a few mindscapes, and I've never seen any...other than mine..."
She nodded. "B-But I'm glad your monsters didn't...you know..."
“...m-me too...they’re r-really sc-scary....they don’t h-hurt me b-b-but....others..”
"S-So...they don't let anyone else in...?"
“Y-Yup....” he taps his fingertips together
“B-But im here now, so that’s a start...”
“Mhmm..” he smiles brightly
She smiled back, hugging him. “I’m really happy you trust me enough to let me in here.”
Iuvenis was suprised at hug, “W-Well....you’re my best f-friend ! Of c-course!”
“B-Best friend...” she repeated, tail swishing happily.
“Uh huh! My B-Bestest F-F-Friend!” He laughed, tail thumping up and down, the star on the tip glowing
“Oh! Your tail, it’s glowing! That’s so cool!!”
“I-It does th-that a l-lot...” he gets embarrassed “your t-tail is coo-l too... you c-c-can fight s-somemun with I-it..!”
"Y-Yeah, I'd rather not, though..." She traced a circle on the station with her tail.
“O-Oh....it’s st-still cool...”
She blushed a bit. “Uh...thanks...”

“N-No problem....” he stutters 
It becomes quite as neither know what to say
“.....w-wanna see i-if I can ma-make big brother a-again?”
“S-Sure!” She nodded, looking a bit excited.
He took a few steps to the pile of goop, holding his hands over it, concentrating on shaping it
She turned around, getting a little closer so she can watch.
The goop started to move and slosh around, slowly starting to morph into a generic mun shape
She smiled, looking excited. Her tail was wagging, but she didn’t want to say anything to break his focus.

His face was scrunched up, focusing a hard amount, as the molds the features of Veteris
Though in his absorption of the moment he failed to hear the sounds of the cracking of joints behind them
Wanderer, however, does hear it, and she turns around.

What she sees are....disturbing creatures
Long slender claws bound together by black straps, thin humanoid bodies contorting in different manners, gaping zipper like mouths, lumpy triangular heads, slowly encroaching.
Wanderer looked scared, but she looked back at Iuvenis, seeing how focused he was.  She readied her spear tail for a fight.

The monsters slowly wobble towards Wanderer, their mouths snapping eagerly as they get *very* close 
Then
A singular, metal, clang.
She stabbed one that got to close for comfort in the chest, more out of panic than actual strategy.

The thing stumbled back from the attack, rearing it’s claws to strike her
A shadowy hand stopped it, the monster suddenly ripped in half. If wanderer were to look behind her, she would see two monsters laying dead(?) on the ground, one having the same fate as this one
“What the-?!” She looked around, trying to find her mysterious ally.

As her eyes dart , the shadowy figure blurred around the void, cutting down the remaining monsters like trees, the few glances she could grab, they did not look familiar at all, Iuvenis, tired from using most of his energy, on the other hand had a excited grin, stars in his eyes. 
The mystery savior finally lands on the station, one of the circles glowing a bright blue, the scythe he was wielding dissipates,  
“V-V-Vet....”
“Vet...?” Wanderer repeated, approaching her powerful new ally.

The shadow looks up at the two kids, apporching Iuvenis, and crouches
Was he smiling? They couldn’t tell, he didn’t really have a mouth, well, a noticeable one, the boys smile was very noticeable however, as shadow cupped his face and gently bonked his head against his, almost if saying, *hey little brother*
“V-Veteris!”
Wanderer watched this, smiling happily.
“A-Ah Wander, this i-is....my bi-big brother.....we-welll...not really...but...” he gestures to the shadowy form.
“Oh! I see! Nice to meet you!” She waved at the shadow.

It looks at her with empty eyes, a cold, silent expression on it ~~just like the real thing~~
It awkwardly mimics her wave
“Hmm...” she giggled. “K-Kinda reminds me of Suzy Q...”
“S-Suzy wh-whozit?” He looks confused as his head tilts
“One of my monsters...the only one who actually notices me.”
“O-Oh.....that Ni-nice I g-g-guess..” the shadow blinked their white eyes in confusion
“...W-Would you like to meet her?”
“I m-mean....wo-would she....a-a-attack me?”

The word attack made the shadow tense up 
Summoning it’s scythe, eyes darting around
“N-No, she wouldn’t!”
“T-Then I g-guess I’d like t-to me-meet her...”
“OK.” She nodded. “She’s in my mindscape. You ready to go?”
“Y-Yup...” he turns to shadow Veteris patting it on the head, “Bye-Bye...” unbeknownst to him, it would not stay in his realm.
She smiled, taking his hand and leading him into ( #aion  ) her mindscape
